        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 6:16PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 616 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles west of Henrys Lake, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southern Madison
and eastern Beaverhead Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
